          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " which began in 2020. The COVID-19 shutdowns caused both a shortage of new vehicles and components, triggering demand on the black market for both. In addition, people cooped-up in their homes, some unable to work after being furloughed began looking for additional sources of income, not all of them through honest work. Bored kids have participated in street takeovers and street racing, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
